(67431,"The Executioners (The Chase, Part One)",766,"<p>The travellers learn from the Time-Space Visualiser taken from theMoroks&apos; museum that Daleks equipped with their own time machine are on their trail with orders to exterminate them. They flee in the TARDIS.</p><p>The chase begins on the desert planet Aridius and takes in a number of stopping-off points, including a spooky haunted house which is actually a futuristic fun-fair attraction.</p><p>Eventually both time machines arrive on the jungle planet Mechanus, where the Daleks try to infiltrate and kill the Doctor&apos;s party with a robotic double of him. The travellers are taken prisoner by the Mechonoids — robots sent some fifty years earlier to prepare landing sites for human colonists who never arrived — and meet Steven Taylor, a stranded astronaut who has been the Mechonoids&apos; captive for the past two years.</p><p>The Daleks and the Mechonoids engage in a fierce battle which ends in their mutual destruction. The Doctor&apos;s party seizes this opportunity to escape. The Doctor reluctantly helps Ian and Barbara to use the Daleks&apos; time machine to return home.</p>",30,2,25,"1965-05-22","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/22/56257.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/67431/doctor-who-2x30-the-executioners-the-chase-part-one"),
