(323199,"The Android Invasion, Part One",766,"<p>The Doctor and Sarah return to Earth in the present day to find a strangely deserted village and woods stalked by white-clad figures.</p>",13,13,25,"1975-11-22","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286543.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323199/doctor-who-13x13-the-android-invasion-part-one"),
(323200,"The Android Invasion, Part Two",766,"<p>The Doctor suspects Crayford brought something to Earth in his rocket, as he and Sarah find themselves hunted by UNIT.</p>",14,13,25,"1975-11-29","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286544.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323200/doctor-who-13x14-the-android-invasion-part-two"),
(323201,"The Android Invasion, Part Three",766,"<p>The Doctor is captured by Styggron and left to die in the destruction of the fake village but Sarah escapes from the disorientation chamber to try and rescue him.</p>",15,13,25,"1975-12-06","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286549.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323201/doctor-who-13x15-the-android-invasion-part-three"),
(323202,"The Android Invasion, Part Four",766,"<p>The Doctor and Sarah reach Earth and try to warn the research centre about the Kraal invasion before Styggron unleashes his virus.</p>",16,13,25,"1975-12-13","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286551.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323202/doctor-who-13x16-the-android-invasion-part-four"),
(323203,"The Brain of Morbius, Part One",766,"<p>The Tardis lands on the bleak planet Karn, in a spaceship graveyard, where The Doctor and Sarah find a evil scientist called Doctor Solon is constructing a new body for the brain of a evil time lord known as Morbius, whom The Doctor thought was executed by the high council on Gallifrey. Where Morbius with his new body plots to rule the galaxy.</p>",17,13,25,"1976-01-03","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286552.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323203/doctor-who-13x17-the-brain-of-morbius-part-one"),
(323204,"The Brain of Morbius, Part Two",766,"<p>The Sisterhood prepare to sacrifice the Doctor to the Sacred Flame and Sarah is injured while rescuing him.</p>",18,13,25,"1976-01-10","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286558.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323204/doctor-who-13x18-the-brain-of-morbius-part-two"),
(323205,"The Brain of Morbius, Part Three",766,"<p>The Doctor attempts to restore the Sacred Flame to prove his good intentions to the Sisterhood, while Solon prepares to connect the brain of Morbius to his body.</p>",19,13,25,"1976-01-17","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286566.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323205/doctor-who-13x19-the-brain-of-morbius-part-three"),
(323206,"The Brain of Morbius, Part Four",766,"<p>Morbius goes on the rampage, forcing the Doctor and Solon to team up to try and bring him back under control.</p>",20,13,25,"1976-01-24","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286571.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323206/doctor-who-13x20-the-brain-of-morbius-part-four"),
(323207,"The Seeds of Doom, Part One",766,"<p>Members of the World Ecology Bureau discover a centuries-old seed pod buried deep in Antarctica&apos;s permafrost. It seems to be still alive, growing without soil. They transmit a photo to London where Richard Dunbar of the W.E.B. shares it with the Doctor. Wary of what it might be, the Doctor immediately flies down with Sarah. They don&apos;t know that Dunbar is a leak in the bureau and has tipped off the discovery to a rich plant fanatic named Harrison Chase. Chase sends a thug and a plant expert down to verify the discovery and fetch it back by any means possible. But before anyone arrives, the pod hatches and the tendril-like life form within attaches itself to one of the men, turning him green. It&apos;s as The Doctor feared: they&apos;re dealing with a Krynoid.</p>",21,13,25,"1976-01-31","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286578.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323207/doctor-who-13x21-the-seeds-of-doom-part-one"),
(323208,"The Seeds of Doom, Part Two",766,"<p>With a killer Krynoid on the loose, the Doctor, Sarah and the last surviving member of the expedition concentrate on hunting it down, unmindful of Chase&apos;s men who, once they learn of the second Krynoid pod (which always travel through space in pairs), work to obtain it and eliminate all possible witnesses.</p>",22,13,25,"1976-02-07","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286582.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323208/doctor-who-13x22-the-seeds-of-doom-part-two"),
(323209,"The Seeds of Doom, Part Three",766,"<p>Surviving two attempts to end their lives, the Doctor and Sarah seek the identity of the plant fanatic who ordered the hit on the arctic base, pursuing their only lead - a commissioned painting of a rare flower left in the boot of a car. Chase, meanwhile, is doing all he can to encourage the hatching of the Krynoid pod.</p>",23,13,25,"1976-02-14","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286584.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323209/doctor-who-13x23-the-seeds-of-doom-part-three"),
(323210,"The Seeds of Doom, Part Four",766,"<p>Sarah is saved from a Krynoid fate and runs off, but the same can&apos;t be said for one of Chase&apos;s men. Not only is he simultaneously devoured and transformed, his fascinated employer will do all he can to encourage the process. The Doctor gets introduced to Chase&apos;s grinder and compost acceleration chamber, which promises him a painful yet swift death en route to making him one with nature, via the garden&apos;s nutrient pump. The situation has finally gone too far for Dunbar, who outs his own involvement in this matter and stands up to Chase, only to come face to face with a fully developed Krynoid.</p>",24,13,25,"1976-02-21","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286589.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323210/doctor-who-13x24-the-seeds-of-doom-part-four"),
(323211,"The Seeds of Doom, Part Five",766,"<p>In the interest of self-preservation, Chase&apos;s men side with The Doctor against the Krynoid, but the Krynoid - now bigger than the Chase Mansion - invites The Doctor to join it, promising to leave the others alone if he does. People within a mile of the Chase Estate, however, start getting strangled by their plants, while Chase, snapping photos of the Krynoid, has a significant one-on-one encounter with it.</p>",25,13,25,"1976-02-28","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286590.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323211/doctor-who-13x25-the-seeds-of-doom-part-five"),
(323212,"The Seeds of Doom, Part Six",766,"<p>Chase is obviously under Krynoid control. The Doctor suspects possession but, with the mountainous Krynoid nearing maturity and whacking the mansion to pieces, he concerns himself with the bigger picture and orders the mansion - with Sarah and him still inside - to be bombed.</p>",26,13,25,"1976-03-06","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286591.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323212/doctor-who-13x26-the-seeds-of-doom-part-six"),
(323213,"The Masque of Mandragora, Part One",766,"<p>The Doctor and Sarah are drawn into the Mandragora Helix, an entity which exists among the stars and which transports the TARDIS to 15th century Italy.</p>",1,14,25,"1976-09-04","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286636.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323213/doctor-who-14x01-the-masque-of-mandragora-part-one"),
(323214,"The Masque of Mandragora, Part Two",766,"<p>The Doctor rushes to rescue Sarah from the Brethren of Demnos while Mandragora tries to bring them under its control.</p>",2,14,25,"1976-09-11","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286640.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323214/doctor-who-14x02-the-masque-of-mandragora-part-two"),
(323215,"The Masque of Mandragora, Part Three",766,"<p>The Doctor saves Giuliano from Federico&apos;s men, then they try to find Sarah, unaware Hieronymous has hypnotised her to kill the Doctor.</p>",3,14,25,"1976-09-18","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286642.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323215/doctor-who-14x03-the-masque-of-mandragora-part-three"),
(323216,"The Masque of Mandragora, Part Four",766,"<p>With Mandragora having taken complete control of the brethren, the Doctor tries to find a way to drain off the Mandragora energy on Earth before it wipes out the guests at Giuliano&apos;s masque.</p>",4,14,25,"1976-09-25","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286674.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323216/doctor-who-14x04-the-masque-of-mandragora-part-four"),
(323217,"The Hand of Fear, Part One",766,"<p>The Doctor and Sarah arrive in a quarry during blasting operations and when Sarah is buried under rubble, she discovers a stone hand.</p>",5,14,25,"1976-10-02","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286684.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323217/doctor-who-14x05-the-hand-of-fear-part-one"),
(323218,"The Hand of Fear, Part Two",766,"<p>The Doctor and Carter attempt to gain the trust of the Nunton staff before Sarah takes the hand into the reactor.</p>",6,14,25,"1976-10-09","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286697.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323218/doctor-who-14x06-the-hand-of-fear-part-two"),
(323219,"The Hand of Fear, Part Three",766,"<p>Eldrad uses the energy from the reactor to regenerate herself and tries to force the Doctor and Sarah to take her back to Kastria.</p>",7,14,25,"1976-10-16","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286699.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323219/doctor-who-14x07-the-hand-of-fear-part-three"),
(323220,"The Hand of Fear, Part Four",766,"<p>The Doctor and Sarah attempt to get Eldrad to the regeneration chamber but Rokon has left traps in their path.</p>",8,14,25,"1976-10-23","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286700.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323220/doctor-who-14x08-the-hand-of-fear-part-four"),
(323221,"The Deadly Assassin, Part One",766,"<p>A mysterious evil is at work on Gallifrey. The President of the Time Lords has been assassinated and the Doctor caught red-handed. An inexorable master plan has been set in motion. There can be no escape</p>",9,14,25,"1976-10-30","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286706.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323221/doctor-who-14x09-the-deadly-assassin-part-one"),
(323222,"The Deadly Assassin, Part Two",766,"<p>The Doctor is arrested for the President&apos;s murder and struggles to avoid his immediate execution.</p>",10,14,25,"1976-11-06","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286712.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323222/doctor-who-14x10-the-deadly-assassin-part-two"),
(323223,"The Deadly Assassin, Part Three",766,"<p>The Doctor battles the assassin inside the matrix dreamscape, while the Master tries to bring about his death in the real world.</p>",11,14,25,"1976-11-13","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286713.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323223/doctor-who-14x11-the-deadly-assassin-part-three"),
(323224,"The Deadly Assassin, Part Four",766,"<p>The Doctor realises the Master is planning to tap into the Time Lords&apos; power source to extend his own life, an act that will destroy all Gallifrey.</p>",12,14,25,"1976-11-20","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286714.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323224/doctor-who-14x12-the-deadly-assassin-part-four"),
(323225,"The Face of Evil, Part One",766,"<p>On a nameless planet in the far future where invisible monsters prowl, the Doctor befriends a warrior woman named Leela, recently banished from her tribe, the Sevateem. She and everyone recognize the Doctor immediately. He is the Evil One who, in their mythology, holds their god Xoanon prisoner and must be destroyed.</p>",13,14,25,"1977-01-01","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286718.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323225/doctor-who-14x13-the-face-of-evil-part-one"),
(323226,"The Face of Evil, Part Two",766,"<p>Despite protestations against being the Evil One, mounting evidence points to the Doctor&apos;s prior involvement with Leela&apos;s people, and an error in judgment he once made in their distant past that puts them all in immediate jeopardy.</p>",14,14,25,"1977-01-08","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286719.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323226/doctor-who-14x14-the-face-of-evil-part-two"),
(323227,"The Face of Evil, Part Three",766,"<p>The Doctor and Leela encounter the placid and mind-powerful Tesh, the complete opposite of the savage Saveteem. They recognize the Doctor, too, but to them he is Lord; however, when it becomes evident the Doctor threatens their living god, Xoanon, the Doctor becomes a marked man.</p>",15,14,25,"1977-01-15","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286741.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323227/doctor-who-14x15-the-face-of-evil-part-three"),
(323228,"The Face of Evil, Part Four",766,"<p>As the Saveteem and Tesh finally close in for a fight to the death, the powerful but long-suffering Xoanon ignores their strife to commit its full resources toward killing the Doctor, even to the extent of destroying everyone.</p>",16,14,25,"1977-01-22","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286742.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323228/doctor-who-14x16-the-face-of-evil-part-four"),
(323229,"The Robots of Death, Part One",766,"<p>The TARDIS materialize aboard a sandminer, a mining ship on a desert planet run by a robot labor force headed by a fairly small but sniping human crew. As one crewman is discovered strangled to death, the Doctor and Leela arrive just in time to become the prime suspects.</p>",17,14,25,"1977-01-29","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286743.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323229/doctor-who-14x17-the-robots-of-death-part-one"),
(323230,"The Robots of Death, Part Two",766,"<p>As the strangulations continue and the humans aren&apos;t sure who to blame, Leela meets up with an anomaly among the robot crew - an inquisitive, supposedly mute single-function labor robot capable of independent reasoning. Meanwhile the Doctor starts looking into the possibility that the murderer is a robot, and another crew member is targeted for death.</p>",18,14,25,"1977-02-05","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286750.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323230/doctor-who-14x18-the-robots-of-death-part-two"),
(323231,"The Robots of Death, Part Three",766,"<p>Hearing about a man who grew up only around robots and who has threatened to start a robot revolution, and who may be aboard the sandminer under an assumed name, the Doctor takes D.84 to seek out a possible secret workshop where he would be restructuring robot programming. Meanwhile, as one crew member suffers a complete mental breakdown, reprogrammed robots are ordered to kill all remaining humans.</p>",19,14,25,"1977-02-12","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286752.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323231/doctor-who-14x19-the-robots-of-death-part-three"),
(323232,"The Robots of Death, Part Four",766,"<p>With secrecy no longer necessary for the robot revolution, Controller Taren Capel shuts down all friendly robots and gives the remaining humans an ultimatum, or else their deaths will be slow and painful. With no conventional weaponry aboard their commercial vessel, the humans do what they can to resist while giving the Doctor time to work out a permanent solution.</p>",20,14,25,"1977-02-19","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286769.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323232/doctor-who-14x20-the-robots-of-death-part-four"),
(323233,"The Talons of Weng-Chiang, Part One",766,"<p>The Doctor and Leela land in Victorian London, and find themselves in the middle of missing girls, mutilated bodies, and vicious Chinese gangs. The Palace theater, presenting hypnotist Li H&apos;sen Chang seems to be at the center of it all.</p>",21,14,25,"1977-02-26","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286775.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323233/doctor-who-14x21-the-talons-of-weng-chiang-part-one"),
(323234,"The Talons of Weng-Chiang, Part Two",766,"<p>After escaping from the vicious giant rat in the sewers, the Doctor &amp; Leela team up with Litefoot. Chang, Mr Sin and Weng-Chiang go in search of the time cabinet, while the Doctor and Jago go in search of Chiang&apos;s lair.</p>",22,14,25,"1977-03-05","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286776.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323234/doctor-who-14x22-the-talons-of-weng-chiang-part-two"),
(323235,"The Talons of Weng-Chiang, Part Three",766,"<p>Leela follows Chang in order to find Greel&apos;s hideout while the Doctor and Litefoot set about finding her.</p>",23,14,25,"1977-03-12","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286796.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323235/doctor-who-14x23-the-talons-of-weng-chiang-part-three"),
(323236,"The Talons of Weng-Chiang, Part Four",766,"<p>Having rescued Leela from the jaws of the giant vicious rat, she &amp; the Doctor dress up and attend Chang&apos;s show at the palace, but end up as part of the act. At home, Litefoot tries to protect the time cabinet.</p>",24,14,25,"1977-03-19","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286799.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323236/doctor-who-14x24-the-talons-of-weng-chiang-part-four"),
(323237,"The Talons of Weng-Chiang, Part Five",766,"<p>Weng-Chiang has stolen the time cabinet from Litefoot&apos;s house, so the Doctor and Leela go to try and stop him from using it. They find an opium-drugged Chang. Jago teams up with Litefoot for their own investigation.</p>",25,14,25,"1977-03-26","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286801.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323237/doctor-who-14x25-the-talons-of-weng-chiang-part-five"),
(323238,"The Talons of Weng-Chiang, Part Six",766,"<p>The real face of Weng-Chiang is revealed as the Doctor, Leela, Jago and Litefoot face their final battle, against both Magnus Greel and a trigger-happy Mr Sin.</p>",26,14,25,"1977-04-02","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286803.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323238/doctor-who-14x26-the-talons-of-weng-chiang-part-six"),
(323239,"Horror of Fang Rock, Part One",766,"<p>The TARDIS lands near an isolated rocky island lighthouse just after a comet strikes the nearby sea and a sudden chilling fog rolls in. Soon after, electrical problems take hold of the generator and one of the keepers dies mysteriously. Rueben, the eldest keeper, thinks it&apos;s the return of the legendary Beast of Fang Rock, but the Doctor suspects it&apos;s something worse that a legend.</p>",1,15,25,"1977-09-03","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286812.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323239/doctor-who-15x01-horror-of-fang-rock-part-one"),
(323240,"Horror of Fang Rock, Part Two",766,"<p>With inexplicable electrical problems keeping the lighthouse from maintaining a steady beam, a foolhardy ship crashes against the island rocks. Four shaken and discontent survivors join the people inside where the Doctor surmises they&apos;re all being carefully scrutinized, a prelude to an attack.</p>",2,15,25,"1977-09-10","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286816.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323240/doctor-who-15x02-horror-of-fang-rock-part-two"),
(323241,"Horror of Fang Rock, Part Three",766,"<p>A death scream is heard, yet all are accounted for. Eventually the Doctor finds a body stashed away but hours old, with rigor mortis already settling in, which means there&apos;s a chameleon in their midst. Completely cut off from the rest of the world and with an escalating body count, the Doctor wonders just what, exactly, he&apos;s locked inside the lighthouse with them all.</p>",3,15,25,"1977-09-17","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286820.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323241/doctor-who-15x03-horror-of-fang-rock-part-three"),
(323242,"Horror of Fang Rock, Part Four",766,"<p>With little to fear, and its mother ship about to land and turn Earth into an alien attack base, the electrically charged Rutan scout drops its human guise and attacks openly.</p>",4,15,25,"1977-09-24","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/286825.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323242/doctor-who-15x04-horror-of-fang-rock-part-four"),
(323243,"The Invisible Enemy, Part One",766,"<p>&quot;Contact has been made!&quot; A relief crew en route to Titan in 5000 AD unwarily pick up hitchhikers that change them. Shortly thereafter the Doctor, passing through the same point in space, is hitchhiked as well, but not Leela - a reject who must die.</p>",5,15,25,"1977-10-01","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/287025.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323243/doctor-who-15x05-the-invisible-enemy-part-one"),
(323244,"The Invisible Enemy, Part Two",766,"<p>The Doctor draws into himself, fighting the voice in his own head that&apos;s trying to take over his intelligence.</p>",6,15,25,"1977-10-08","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/287029.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323244/doctor-who-15x06-the-invisible-enemy-part-two"),
(323245,"The Invisible Enemy, Part Three",766,"<p>The medical center mounts a defense against alien forces trying to take the comatose Doctor while clones of Leela and the Doctor go microscopic so they can hunt down the intelligent infection that&apos;s in his head.</p>",7,15,25,"1977-10-15","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/287032.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323245/doctor-who-15x07-the-invisible-enemy-part-three"),
(323246,"The Invisible Enemy, Part Four",766,"<p>In trying to retrieve the clones from inside the Doctor, the alien virus is brought from the microbial world into the macro-world, and it&apos;s ready to spawn.</p>",8,15,25,"1977-10-22","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/287034.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323246/doctor-who-15x08-the-invisible-enemy-part-four"),
(323247,"Image of the Fendahl, Part One",766,"<p>Archeologists near a reputedly haunted woods use a time scanner to explore the history of a sinister 12 million year old skull, creating a hole in time that attracts the Doctor&apos;s attention.</p>",9,15,25,"1977-10-29","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/82/205159.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323247/doctor-who-15x09-image-of-the-fendahl-part-one"),
(323248,"Image of the Fendahl, Part Two",766,"<p>Every time the archaeologists explore the ancient skull, something deadly hunts and haunts the wood while one of the researchers is particularly affected.</p>",10,15,25,"1977-11-05","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/82/205177.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323248/doctor-who-15x10-image-of-the-fendahl-part-two");
REPLACE INTO episode VALUES
(323249,"Image of the Fendahl, Part Three",766,"<p>The Doctor endeavors to prevent the re-existence of a Fendahl, a group entity that feeds on life itself and thought only to exist in Time Lord mythology, but a witches&apos; coven, seeking power, intervenes.</p>",11,15,25,"1977-11-12","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/82/205189.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323249/doctor-who-15x11-image-of-the-fendahl-part-three"),
(323250,"Image of the Fendahl, Part Four",766,"<p>With one of the archaeologists transformed and a massive implosion threatening, the Fendahl and its Fendahleen components start coming into existence while the Doctor, Leela and the Tylers do what they can to stop it.</p>",12,15,25,"1977-11-19","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/82/205196.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323250/doctor-who-15x12-image-of-the-fendahl-part-four"),
(323251,"The Sun Makers, Part One",766,"<p>The Tardis lands on Pluto in the far future. Instead of being a lifeless rock, there&apos;s scented air, massive buildings, six suns, a human population subjugated by crippling taxes from a government called &quot;The Company,&quot; and a man about to commit suicide.</p>",13,15,25,"1977-11-26","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/114/287051.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323251/doctor-who-15x13-the-sun-makers-part-one"),
(323252,"The Sun Makers, Part Two",766,"<p>Captured by the authorities, the Doctor finds himself restrained in a Correction Centre where he&apos;s to be prepped for painful shock treatments, making him unable to return within a given time frame to the underground rebels holding Leela, who are prepared to kill her as promised.</p>",14,15,25,"1977-12-03","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/115/287932.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323252/doctor-who-15x14-the-sun-makers-part-two"),
(323254,"The Sun Makers, Part Three",766,"<p>The merciless Collector, who runs The Company, issues a bounty on the Doctor for his capture, while an already captured Leela is sentenced to public execution, via a steamer, for crimes against the company.</p>",15,15,25,"1977-12-10","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/115/287933.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323254/doctor-who-15x15-the-sun-makers-part-three"),
(323255,"The Sun Makers, Part Four",766,"<p>Attempting to start a successful revolution, the Doctor uses Pluto&apos;s Public Address System to announce successful revolution, all the while trying to determine the Collector&apos;s true species and why he, or it, seems set on taxing the life out of humans.</p>",16,15,25,"1977-12-17","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/115/287934.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323255/doctor-who-15x16-the-sun-makers-part-four"),
(323256,"Underworld, Part One",766,"<p>Materializing at the edge of the cosmos, the frontier of creation, The Doctor, Leela &amp; K-9 encounter four ancient space travelers from Minyos, the first race ever contacted by the Time Lords. All but extinct due to their Time Lords encounter, the Minyans (rejuvenated 1000 times each) have been embarked on a long 100,000 year old quest, searching the universe for the lost race bank of their species to take to a new home world. But their equally old ship is finally failing, succumbing to the gravitational pull of a newly forming sun and taking the Doctor and his party with it.</p>",17,15,25,"1978-01-07","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/115/287935.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323256/doctor-who-15x17-underworld-part-one"),
(323257,"Underworld, Part Two",766,"<p>Crashing inside a newly formed planet, the Doctor and others find it inhabited by a slave labor mining society, where rocks are harvested for their radioactive energy and human life has little value. With a population controlled by deliberate cave-ins, poison gas, and periodic sacrifices to an Oracle, the miners, called Trogs, are also descendants from Minyos, and who desperately desire freedom.</p>",18,15,25,"1978-01-14","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/115/287936.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323257/doctor-who-15x18-underworld-part-two"),
(323258,"Underworld, Part Three",766,"<p>Capturing the Doctor and Leela, the citadel guards are quite pleased to have more subjects for their public executions, but it only fires up a Trog revolt instead.</p>",19,15,25,"1978-01-21","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/115/287937.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323258/doctor-who-15x19-underworld-part-three"),
(323259,"Underworld, Part Four",766,"<p>With the Trog revolt close to success, the Oracle grants the Minyos travelers what they seek (the long lost race bank) in hopes they&apos;ll depart peacefully and straight away, but the Doctor suspects it&apos;s not all going to be as amicable as that. And what to do about the Trogs?</p>",20,15,25,"1978-01-28","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/115/287938.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323259/doctor-who-15x20-underworld-part-four"),
(323260,"The Invasion of Time, Part One",766,"<p>The Doctor returns to Gallifrey to become the President of the High Council of Time Lords. But Leela realizes that the Doctor is acting out of character.</p>",21,15,25,"1978-02-04","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/115/287954.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323260/doctor-who-15x21-the-invasion-of-time-part-one"),
(323261,"The Invasion of Time, Part Two",766,"<p>The Doctor orders Leela exiled from the Capitol, then orders K9 to sabotage Gallifrey&apos;s defences.</p>",22,15,25,"1978-02-11","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/115/287956.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323261/doctor-who-15x22-the-invasion-of-time-part-two"),
(323262,"The Invasion of Time, Part Three",766,"<p>The Doctor allows the Vardans to occupy Gallifrey while Leela and Rodan head out into the wasteland to search for help.</p>",23,15,25,"1978-02-18","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/115/287957.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323262/doctor-who-15x23-the-invasion-of-time-part-three"),
(323263,"The Invasion of Time, Part Four",766,"<p>The Doctor convinces Andred to trust him as he works to expel the Vardans, while Leela gathers the Outsiders for an attack on the Capitol.</p>",24,15,25,"1978-02-25","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/115/287958.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323263/doctor-who-15x24-the-invasion-of-time-part-four"),
(323264,"The Invasion of Time, Part Five",766,"<p>The Doctor and his friends flee from the Sontarans and the Doctor tries to convince Borusa to abandon his sacred office in order to help defeat them.</p>",25,15,25,"1978-03-04","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/115/287969.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323264/doctor-who-15x25-the-invasion-of-time-part-five"),
(323265,"The Invasion of Time, Part Six",766,"<p>The Doctor and his friends take refuge in the TARDIS but find themselves pursued by Stor and Kelner.</p>",26,15,25,"1978-03-11","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/115/287970.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323265/doctor-who-15x26-the-invasion-of-time-part-six"),
(323267,"The Ribos Operation, Part One",766,"<p>The Guardian of Time gives the Doctor a difficult task,and a new assistant. Together they must search for the six segments of the Key to Time, to prevent the Universe from being plunged into eternal chaos. On their mission, the Doctor and Romana travel to the planet Ribos where the first segment of the key is protected by the monstrous Shrivenzale.</p>",1,16,25,"1978-09-02","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/115/287971.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323267/doctor-who-16x01-the-ribos-operation-part-one"),
(323268,"The Ribos Operation, Part Two",766,"<p>The Doctor and Romana investigate Garron&apos;s activities but this results in the Graff believing they are working together.</p>",2,16,25,"1978-09-09","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/115/287974.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323268/doctor-who-16x02-the-ribos-operation-part-two"),
(323269,"The Ribos Operation, Part Three",766,"<p>The Graff takes the Doctor, Romana and Garron prisoner and then sets about trying to track down Unstoffe and the jethryk.</p>",3,16,25,"1978-09-16","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/115/288395.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323269/doctor-who-16x03-the-ribos-operation-part-three"),
(323270,"The Ribos Operation, Part Four",766,"<p>The Doctor returns to the city to keep an eye on the Graff, leaving Romana, K9 and Garron to search for Unstoffe and the first segment. However, Garron double crosses them and steals the tracer.</p>",4,16,25,"1978-09-23","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/115/288396.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323270/doctor-who-16x04-the-ribos-operation-part-four"),
(323271,"The Pirate Planet, Part One",766,"<p>In seeking the second segment of the Key to Time, the TARDIS heads for an icy world but lands on a populated planet that shouldn&apos;t be there.</p>",5,16,25,"1978-09-30","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/115/288401.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323271/doctor-who-16x05-the-pirate-planet-part-one"),
(323272,"The Pirate Planet, Part Two",766,"<p>After the Mentiads knock the Doctor out, he discovers that Romana has been taken to the planets bridge. He then travels to the bridge to help her and ends up being forced to help repair the engines.</p>",6,16,25,"1978-10-07","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/141/353443.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323272/doctor-who-16x06-the-pirate-planet-part-two"),
(323274,"The Pirate Planet, Part Three",766,"<p>The Doctor takes Romana down to investigate the planets mines and gets unexpected help when the Captains guards show up to confront them.</p>",7,16,25,"1978-10-14","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/141/353447.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323274/doctor-who-16x07-the-pirate-planet-part-three"),
(323275,"The Pirate Planet, Part Four",766,"<p>The Mentiads with the help of the Doctor work to foil Queen Xanxia&apos;s plan to regain a body and destroy Earth in the process.</p>",8,16,25,"1978-10-21","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/141/353452.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323275/doctor-who-16x08-the-pirate-planet-part-four"),
(323276,"The Stones of Blood, Part One",766,"<p>In their search for the 3rd segment of the key to time, the Doctor and Romana land on Earth at a Stonehenge type site where worshipers are engaged in their practice and people are being killed by unknown causes. While en route the Doctor and Romana hear a strange voice that says &apos;Beware the Black Guardian&quot;.</p>",9,16,25,"1978-10-28","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/142/356419.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323276/doctor-who-16x09-the-stones-of-blood-part-one"),
(323278,"The Stones of Blood, Part Two",766,"<p>Romana ends up hanging on the side of a cliff while the Doctor is captured by Druid pagan worshipers. The Doctor and the Professor then go on a search for Romana after finding her shoes.</p>",10,16,25,"1978-11-04","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/142/356418.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323278/doctor-who-16x10-the-stones-of-blood-part-two"),
(323279,"The Stones of Blood, Part Three",766,"<p>The Doctor transfers to Hyperspace to save Romana from her imprisonment and has a run in with the Megara Justice machines during his search.</p>",11,16,25,"1978-11-11","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/142/356420.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323279/doctor-who-16x11-the-stones-of-blood-part-three"),
(323280,"The Stones of Blood, Part Four",766,"<p>The Doctor convinces the Megara to give Vivien Fay a truth test while playing for time so Romana can get back to Earth and find evidence against Vivien.</p>",12,16,25,"1978-11-18","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/142/356424.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323280/doctor-who-16x12-the-stones-of-blood-part-four"),
(323282,"The Androids of Tara, Part One",766,"<p>The Doctor and Romana are now searching for the 3rd segment of the Key to Time. Landing on the world of Tara, the Doctor decides to send Romana off in search of the 3rd segment while he takes a break and does some fishing.</p>",13,16,25,"1978-11-25","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/143/359165.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323282/doctor-who-16x13-the-androids-of-tara-part-one"),
(323283,"The Androids of Tara, Part Two",766,"<p>Romana is being held prisoner by Count Grendal, the Prince and his men along with the Doctor are drugged when they toast to the king after the Doctor has fixed the Prince&apos;s android. He is then accused of being involved in the Princes disappearance. They then have to figure out a plan to still get the android crowned as the Prince has vanished while the men were unconscious.</p>",14,16,25,"1978-12-02","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/143/359167.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323283/doctor-who-16x14-the-androids-of-tara-part-two"),
(323284,"The Androids of Tara, Part Three",766,"<p>The confirmation of the King has been put on hold, and the Doctor works on repairing the android of the future king in time. Count Grendal meanwhile, having had his plans interrupted works to stop the confirmation so he can become king in the Princes place.</p>",15,16,25,"1978-12-09","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/143/359182.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323284/doctor-who-16x15-the-androids-of-tara-part-three"),
(323286,"The Androids of Tara, Part Four",766,"<p>After the Doctor escapes Grendel&apos;s trap, plans are made to rescue both the Prince and Strella. Count Grendel continues to finalize his plan to take over the kingship.</p>",16,16,25,"1978-12-16","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/143/359183.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323286/doctor-who-16x16-the-androids-of-tara-part-four"),
(323287,"The Power of Kroll, Part One",766,"<p>The Doctor and Romana land on the moon Delta III, home to the green-skinned Swampies and a small group of human colonists. Soon after arriving, Romana is taken by the Swampies who wish to sacrifice her to the mysterious squid-like Kroll.</p>",17,16,25,"1978-12-23",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323287/doctor-who-16x17-the-power-of-kroll-part-one"),
(323288,"The Power of Kroll, Part Two",766,"<p>The Doctor rescues Romana from the Swampies but is horrified to hear that Kroll has awoken.</p>",18,16,25,"1978-12-30",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323288/doctor-who-16x18-the-power-of-kroll-part-two"),
(323289,"The Power of Kroll, Part Three",766,"<p>The Doctor, Romana and Rohm-Dutt are sentenced to death by the Swampies while the refinery crew try to work out a way to destroy Kroll.</p>",19,16,25,"1979-01-06",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323289/doctor-who-16x19-the-power-of-kroll-part-three"),
(323290,"The Power of Kroll, Part Four",766,"<p>The Doctor races to stop Thawn from destroying the Swampie settlement and then works to destroy Kroll once and for all.</p>",20,16,25,"1979-01-13",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323290/doctor-who-16x20-the-power-of-kroll-part-four"),
(323291,"The Armageddon Factor, Part One",766,"<p>In their search for the final segment of the &apos;Key To Time&apos;, the Doctor and Romana land the TARDIS on the world of Atrios who is at war with it&apos;s neighboring planet Zeos. Upon avoiding a missile attack right before landing, the Doctor and Time Lady Romana are then mistaken for spys from Zeos by the Marshall.</p>",21,16,25,"1979-01-20","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/146/367448.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323291/doctor-who-16x21-the-armageddon-factor-part-one"),
(323292,"The Armageddon Factor, Part Two",766,"<p>When the Doctor and Romana work to escape they Marshal, they not only discover that their TARDIS has been buried underneath a pile of rubble from a recent Zeos attack, but also they discover someone who may be trapped and kidnapped by a unknown source.</p>",22,16,25,"1979-01-27","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/147/367674.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323292/doctor-who-16x22-the-armageddon-factor-part-two"),
(323293,"The Armageddon Factor, Part Three",766,"<p>While faithful K-9 awaits the return of the Doctor and those with him, he is taken prisoner by The Shadow. With The Marshal determined to attack Zeos, the Doctor has to put a halt to his plan in order to save Atrios and billions of lives. </p>",23,16,25,"1979-02-03","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/147/367677.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323293/doctor-who-16x23-the-armageddon-factor-part-three"),
(323294,"The Armageddon Factor, Part Four",766,"<p>K-9 communicates with the leader of the Zeos world and the Doctor attempts to keep the leader from completing it&apos;s plan. The Doctor and companions discover the unknown world that is between Atrios and Zeos.</p>",24,16,25,"1979-02-10","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/147/367680.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323294/doctor-who-16x24-the-armageddon-factor-part-four"),
(323295,"The Armageddon Factor, Part Five",766,"<p>The Doctor with Drax&apos;s help, escape from their prison and work to stop The Shadows plan. The Shadow uses Astra to further the Black Guardians plot to obtain the Key to Time.</p>",25,16,25,"1979-02-17","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/147/367683.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323295/doctor-who-16x25-the-armageddon-factor-part-five"),
(323296,"The Armageddon Factor, Part Six",766,"<p>The Doctor and Romana prevent the Marshal from concluding his plan and discover what the last segment of the Key to Time actually is. They then encounter both the Black Guardian and The White Guardian in their effort to conclude the mission given to them by the White Guardian.</p>",26,16,25,"1979-02-24","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/147/367684.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323296/doctor-who-16x26-the-armageddon-factor-part-six"),
(323299,"Destiny of the Daleks, Part One",766,"<p>Romana experiments with regeneration while the Doctor prepares to land on a world that is experiencing periodic earthquakes and seems strangely familiar to him.</p>",1,17,25,"1979-09-01","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/266/666519.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323299/doctor-who-17x01-destiny-of-the-daleks-part-one"),
(323300,"Destiny of the Daleks, Part Two",766,"<p>After discovering that the world they are on is the Dalek&apos;s home planet of Skaro, the Doctor starts to question the reason for the Movellans being there. Meanwhile, Romana is captured by the Daleks.</p>",2,17,25,"1979-09-08","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/266/666518.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323300/doctor-who-17x02-destiny-of-the-daleks-part-two"),
(323302,"Destiny of the Daleks, Part Three",766,"<p>The Doctor arrives at Davros&apos;s hidden location in the bunker ahead of the Daleks, and questions Davros about how he has survived all this time. The Doctor then threatens his way out. Romana is taken hostage by the Movellans in order to get the Doctor to submit to their will while the Doctor confirms his suspicions about the Movellans.</p>",3,17,25,"1979-09-15","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/274/685429.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323302/doctor-who-17x03-destiny-of-the-daleks-part-three"),
(323303,"Destiny of the Daleks, Part Four",766,"<p>To break the centuries-old stalemate in their war, the Movellans need the Doctor, as do the Daleks need Davros. The solution is simple, but neither side can see it, nor would the Doctor upset this perfect and unplanned peace they&apos;ve achieved. Davros, though, is another matter.</p>",4,17,25,"1979-09-22",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323303/doctor-who-17x04-destiny-of-the-daleks-part-four"),
(323304,"City of Death, Part One",766,"<p>While sightseeing in Paris, the Doctor and Romana find themselves repeatedly reliving the same moments in time. A visit to the Louvre Museum leads the Doctor to suspect an alien plot to steal the Mona Lisa</p>",5,17,25,"1979-09-29","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/158/396646.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323304/doctor-who-17x05-city-of-death-part-one"),
(323305,"City of Death, Part Two",766,"<p>Count Scarlioni has the Doctor, Romana and Duggan locked in his basement but the trio manage to escape and learn of the Count&apos;s experiments with time travel. Even more surprising are his multiple genuine copies of the Mona Lisa.</p>",6,17,25,"1979-10-06",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323305/doctor-who-17x06-city-of-death-part-two"),
(323307,"City of Death, Part Three",766,"<p>Travelling back in time to 1505 Florence in search of Leonardo da Vinci, the Doctor is surprised to instead find Count Scarlioni under a different name. Back in 1979, Romana and Duggan attempt to stop the Count&apos;s heist but arrive too late.</p>",7,17,25,"1979-10-13",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323307/doctor-who-17x07-city-of-death-part-three"),
(323308,"City of Death, Part Four",766,"<p>Count Scarlioni reveals his true form as Scaroth, the last of the Jagaroth and uses his time machine to go back in time and rewrite history. The Doctor, Romana and Duggan take to the Tardis in a race against time to stop him.</p>",8,17,25,"1979-10-20",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323308/doctor-who-17x08-city-of-death-part-four"),
(323310,"The Creature from the Pit, Part One",766,"<p>After Romana finds a distress signal part for the TARDIS&apos;s control console, the Doctor and Romana follow the signal to the world of Chloris. There the Doctor is taken prisoner after he discovers a strange object in a Death Zone and brought to the ruthless Lady Adastra. Meanwhile, Romana is taken prisoner by a tribe of savage men.</p>",9,17,25,"1979-10-27",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323310/doctor-who-17x09-the-creature-from-the-pit-part-one"),
(323311,"The Creature from the Pit, Part Two",766,"<p>The Doctor escapes Lady Adastra by jumping down the pit into the only metal mine on Chloris, there he encounters a astrologer that was thrown into the mine by Adastra and is still alive. Meanwhile Romana is coerced by Lady Adastra to reveal the secret of the giant egg like object.</p>",10,17,25,"1979-11-03",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323311/doctor-who-17x10-the-creature-from-the-pit-part-two"),
(323312,"The Creature from the Pit, Part Three",766,"<p>While in the pit. the Doctor with the help of the old astrologer, seeks to establish what the creature is. While attempting to make contact with the strange creature Lady Adastra and her entourage arrive in the mine in search of the Doctor who they now believe might possibly still be alive. Meanwhile, the tribe of savage men raids the home of Lady Adastra of her metals.</p>",11,17,25,"1979-11-10",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323312/doctor-who-17x11-the-creature-from-the-pit-part-three"),
(323313,"The Creature from the Pit, Part Four",766,"<p>Erato is now able to communicate and the deadly results of Adrasta&apos;s betrayal is disclosed. Erato&apos;s ship has been sending a distress signal for the last 15 years of his captivity and his brethren back home have put a terrible retribution for Adastra&apos;s world in motion.</p>",12,17,25,"1979-11-17",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323313/doctor-who-17x12-the-creature-from-the-pit-part-four"),
(323314,"Nightmare of Eden, Part One",766,"<p>Two spaceships have a hyperspace collision and become locked together causing the area where they are connected to become unstable due to the intersection of the hyperspace fields. The Doctor and Romana arrive and become involved. The Doctor discovers a crewman using the dangerous drug Vraxoin.</p>",13,17,25,"1979-11-24",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323314/doctor-who-17x13-nightmare-of-eden-part-one"),
(323315,"Nightmare of Eden, Part Two",766,"<p>The Doctor and Romana are horrified when they discover that Tryst has live lifeforms stored in his CET machine. The Doctor and Romana continue their search for the narcotic smuggler. When law enforcement officers show up on the ship, the Doctor and Romana immediately become suspects due to their lack of any identity documentation and flee.</p>",14,17,25,"1979-12-01",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323315/doctor-who-17x14-nightmare-of-eden-part-two"),
(323317,"Nightmare of Eden, Part Three",766,"<p>While being chased by the customs officials as smugglers, the  Doctor and Romana work to both track down the smuggler and to separate the two ships. During all this excitement, multiple Mandrels have escaped from the CET machine and the Doctor discovers their secret.</p>",15,17,25,"1979-12-08",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323317/doctor-who-17x15-nightmare-of-eden-part-three"),
(323318,"Nightmare of Eden, Part Four",766,"<p>The Doctor solves the problem of who the smugglers are and how they are transferring the drugs. With the help of the Doctor and Romana, Stott and Fisk make plans to capture the culprits before they can escape.</p>",16,17,25,"1979-12-15",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323318/doctor-who-17x16-nightmare-of-eden-part-four"),
(323319,"The Horns of Nimon, Part One",766,"<p>The Doctor decides to modify some of the TARDIS&apos;s systems, so disables most of the major ships systems. During this process, they encounter a stranded ship from Skonnos. They the assist the remaining crew member who then kidnaps Romana and leaves the Doctor stranded in the TARDIS.</p>",17,17,25,"1979-12-22",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323319/doctor-who-17x17-the-horns-of-nimon-part-one"),
(323320,"The Horns of Nimon, Part Two",766,"<p>Upon arriving on Skonnos, Romana and the Athenian sacrifices are forced into the power complex of the Nimon. The Doctor then arrives on Skonnos searching for the missing Romana.</p>",18,17,25,"1979-12-29",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323320/doctor-who-17x18-the-horns-of-nimon-part-two"),
(323322,"The Horns of Nimon, Part Three",766,"<p>As they travel deeper into the Nimon power complex, the Doctor and Romana start to suspect that there is a lot more to the Nimon than meets the eye and that they may be seeing the start of a invasion of the planet Skonnos.</p>",19,17,25,"1980-01-05",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323322/doctor-who-17x19-the-horns-of-nimon-part-three"),
(323323,"The Horns of Nimon, Part Four",766,"<p>Arriving on the dying world of Crinoth at the other end of the black hole transmat system the Nimon has built, Romana discovers the truth behind the motives of the Nimon and their promises to the people of Skonnos. The Doctor then attempts to foil the invasion plans before the Nimon horde can arrive.</p>",20,17,25,"1980-01-12",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323323/doctor-who-17x20-the-horns-of-nimon-part-four"),
(323325,"Shada, Part One",766,"<p>The Doctor and Romana visit Chronotis, a retired Time Lord living in Cambridge, who admits that he&apos;s lost a book dating back to the time of Rassilon and needs their help to find it. In fact, he&apos;s accidentally lent it out to graduate student Chris Parsons, who soon realizes that this is an extraordinary text indeed. The book is also sought by the evil scientist Skagra, who has developed a sphere capable of drawing its victims&apos; minds out of their bodies. Skagra needs the book to reach the Time Lord prison Shada, which even the Time Lords have forgotten. Long ago they imprisoned the criminal Salyavin there, as punishment for using his powers to transfer his mind into other people&apos;s bodies. Chronotis is eventually forced to admit that he himself is Salyavin; he escaped long ago and used his powers to cause the Time Lords to forget about his prison. However, he&apos;s now repented of his crimes and wishes to live a quiet, peaceful life. Skagra drains Chronotis&apos;s mind and thus acquires the ability to transfer his own mind into other bodies; with the aid of the sphere and his crystalline servants, the Krargs, he will spread his own mind throughout the Universe and become immortal. However, when the Doctor pretends to be stupid, the sphere fails to drain his mind completely. He thus survives, and since there&apos;s a copy of his mind inside the sphere, he is able to use the resonance to turn Skagra&apos;s possessed slaves against him. Skagra is imprisoned by his own Ship, and Chronotis returns to Earth to resume his peaceful retirement.</p>",21,17,25,null,null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323325/doctor-who-17x21-shada-part-one"),
(323326,"Shada, Part Two",766,"<p>See Shada, Part One for the full summary of all six Parts.</p>",22,17,25,null,null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323326/doctor-who-17x22-shada-part-two"),
(323327,"Shada, Part Three",766,"<p>See Shada, Part One for the full summary of all six Parts.</p>",23,17,25,null,null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323327/doctor-who-17x23-shada-part-three"),
(323328,"Shada, Part Four",766,"<p>See Shada, Part One for the full summary of all six Parts.</p>",24,17,25,null,null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323328/doctor-who-17x24-shada-part-four"),
(323329,"Shada, Part Five",766,"<p>See Shada, Part One for the full summary of all six Parts.</p>",25,17,25,null,null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323329/doctor-who-17x25-shada-part-five"),
(323330,"Shada, Part Six",766,"<p>See Shada, Part One for the full summary of all six Parts.</p>",26,17,25,null,null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323330/doctor-who-17x26-shada-part-six"),
(323324,"The Leisure Hive, Part One",766,"<p>Finding out-of-season Brighton beach somewhat lacking, the Doctor and Romana travel to the leisure planet Argolis - but there strange experiments are taking place.</p>",1,18,25,"1980-08-30",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323324/doctor-who-18x01-the-leisure-hive-part-one"),
(323331,"The Leisure Hive, Part Two",766,"<p>Another man is found dead, strangled by the Doctor&apos;s scarf, so the Doctor is put on trial. By some of the archaic rules of law, he&apos;s made to &quot;prove&quot; his innocence by becoming a test subject in a new tachyon experiment with time. The result will prove his innocence or guilt, so they say.</p>",2,18,25,"1980-09-06",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323331/doctor-who-18x02-the-leisure-hive-part-two"),
(323332,"The Leisure Hive, Part Three",766,"<p>With the Doctor suffering from the time experiment, the clandestine schemes of others start coming to light, along with the secreted purposes to which the tachyonic generator has been used.</p>",3,18,25,"1980-09-13",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323332/doctor-who-18x03-the-leisure-hive-part-three"),
(323333,"The Leisure Hive, Part Four",766,"<p>With the saboteur and murderer revealed and arrested, peace should now be restored, but a new threat emerges - a war-monger who&apos;s both ready and eager to aggress upon other worlds with a newly manufactured warrior army.</p>",4,18,25,"1980-09-20",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323333/doctor-who-18x04-the-leisure-hive-part-four"),
(323334,"Meglos, Part One",766,"<p>The Doctor, Romana and K-9 arrive on the forest planet Tygella, where the native Tygellans now live in a underground city, due to the carnivorous plants. Where the Doctor finds he has been wrongly accused of stealing the Dodechedron, the city&apos;s power source. Only to discover the culprit is Meglos, the cactus-like last survivor of the desert planet Zolfa-Thura and he bids to return the Dodechedron to Zolfa-Thura for his own evil purpose and plans to use it as a powerful weapon and he plans to wipe out Tigella.</p>",5,18,25,"1980-09-27","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/357/894934.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323334/doctor-who-18x05-meglos-part-one"),
(323335,"Meglos, Part Two",766,"<p>With the TARDIS occupants trapped in a chronic histeratic loop (forever reliving the same moment in time), the devious Meglos - disguised as the Doctor - gains the trust of the Tigellans along with full and private access to their power chamber.</p>",6,18,25,"1980-10-04","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/357/894936.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323335/doctor-who-18x06-meglos-part-two"),
(323336,"Meglos, Part Three",766,"<p>With the dodecahedron gone, the city goes power critical. Its death, imminent. With Romana seeking escape from Meglos&apos; pirates, and Meglos seeking escape from the sealed-up city, and the Doctor himself seeking to understand what&apos;s been going on (and why everybody wants him arrested), religious factions move in to take over the city.</p>",7,18,25,"1980-10-11","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/357/894939.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323336/doctor-who-18x07-meglos-part-three"),
(323337,"Meglos, Part Four",766,"<p>With the Doctor about to be ritualistically sacrificed to appease the god Ti for stealing the dodecahedron, Meglos and the pirates return to Zolfa-Thura with the dodecahedron to fire up an ancient weapon and blast Tigella out of existence.</p>",8,18,25,"1980-10-18","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/357/894941.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323337/doctor-who-18x08-meglos-part-four"),
(323338,"Full Circle, Part One",766,"<p>In answer to a summons from the Time Lords, the Doctor heads the TARDIS for Gallifrey where he must return Romana, but having tasted adventure and seen foreign worlds, she&apos;s none too happy about the return. Their journey, however, is interrupted by a rare space/time phenomena that lands them - not on Gallifrey - but on Alzarius. There, humanoid inhabitants begin to encounter an infrequent but regular cycle of perilous weather, called Mistfall, that coincides with the emergence of dangerous creatures.</p>",9,18,25,"1980-10-25","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/357/894942.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323338/doctor-who-18x09-full-circle-part-one"),
(323339,"Full Circle, Part Two",766,"<p>As the humanoid community takes refuge in their crashed spaceship, venomous marsh spiders begin to hatch from the local fruit while bestial marshmen emerge from the waters to walk the land. It is quite apparent that the marshmen desire entry into the spaceship. Meanwhile, as a curious marshchild shadows the Doctor, a group of teen rebels decides to take over the TARDIS.</p>",10,18,25,"1980-11-01",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323339/doctor-who-18x10-full-circle-part-two"),
(323340,"Full Circle, Part Three",766,"<p>Infection from a spider bite causes Romana&apos;s personality to change. Meanwhile the Doctor, after discovering that the spaceship society is in a perpetual state of repair and upgrade, has morality issues with the ship&apos;s leading scientist who readies himself to perform gruesome experiments on the live marshchild while it&apos;s fully conscious.</p>",11,18,25,"1980-11-08",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323340/doctor-who-18x11-full-circle-part-three"),
(323341,"Full Circle, Part Four",766,"<p>Marshmen invade the Terradonian ship thanks to Romana, who seems to be in communion with them. While the ship&apos;s inhabitants flee for their lives, the Doctor discovers a crucial fact why these humanoids can never return to the planet Terradon.</p>",12,18,25,"1980-11-15",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323341/doctor-who-18x12-full-circle-part-four"),
(323342,"State of Decay, Part One",766,"<p>The Doctor and Romana find an isolated planet. K9 scans the planet, finding it has a village. The Doctor and Romana find high technology readings with the TARDIS sensors even though the village appears to have an absence of technology. The TARDIS lands near the village. The Doctor and Romana set off, leaving K9 behind to guard the TARDIS. Adric, from the previous story, has stowed away on the TARDIS. K9 finds him, but Adric tells him that as he is a stowaway. The Doctor and Romana find two men arguing. The Doctor asks to speak to a scientist. One of the men mistakes them for lords. After the Doctor, Romana and one of the men leave, The other man, using a radio, calls to others and tells them of the two strangers who just arrived. Travelling through the forest, Romana and the Doctor are surrounded by men. They surrender and are taken to a hidden cave, where they meet the rebels. One man is trying to get a computer up and running. The Doctor helps him and Romana identifies the computer system as coming from Earth, Adric tries to steal some food in the village. Adric is caught and those who caught him take on pity him and offer him a place to sleep because of the evil things that happen at night. The Doctor and Romana appear to be attacked by a swarm of bats at the end.</p>",13,18,25,"1980-11-22",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323342/doctor-who-18x13-state-of-decay-part-one"),
(323343,"State of Decay, Part Two",766,"<p>The Doctor and Romana are taken to the tower where they meet The Lords and come to the realization that the tower is actually a disused spaceship. A Lord named Aukon arrives at the village and takes Adric with him back to the tower.</p>",14,18,25,"1980-11-29",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323343/doctor-who-18x14-state-of-decay-part-two"),
(323344,"State of Decay, Part Three",766,"<p>Tarak arrives to free the Doctor and Romana from their imprisonment. Believing The Lords to be vampires from Gallifreyan legend, the Doctor returns to the Tardis to consult the Record of Rassilon while Tarak and Romana search for Adric.</p>",15,18,25,"1980-12-06",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323344/doctor-who-18x15-state-of-decay-part-three"),
(323345,"State of Decay, Part Four",766,"<p>The Lords prepare to sacrifice Romana and induct Adric into their ranks as part of their plan to awaken the &quot;Great One&quot; and escape E-Space. Meanwhile the Doctor and K9 assist Kalmar&apos;s men in attacking the tower.</p>",16,18,25,"1980-12-13",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323345/doctor-who-18x16-state-of-decay-part-four"),
(323346,"Warriors&apos; Gate, Part One",766,"<p>While the Doctor and Romana desperately rack their brains over how to escape E-Space, Time Winds strike the TARDIS, damaging it and K-9. Strangest of all, it allows Biroc, a hurt and hunted lion-man, to enter, phased in time, and set the control coordinates at zero-zero, sending the TARDIS into a milk-white void. Before running off, he warns of others who will be soon following.</p>",17,18,25,"1981-01-03",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323346/doctor-who-18x17-warriors-gate-part-one"),
(323347,"Warriors&apos; Gate, Part Two",766,"<p>Three humorless men from a damaged bulk freighter find the TARDIS. Wearily, Romana returns with them to appraise the situation of their damaged ship but, because she&apos;s a time sensitive, winds up as a living navigational component to replace their time-sensitive Tharil (lion-man) who escaped. Meanwhile the Doctor, having found a gateway, is having a time with Gundans, robot soldiers programmed to kill.</p>",18,18,25,"1981-01-10",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323347/doctor-who-18x18-warriors-gate-part-two"),
(323348,"Warriors&apos; Gate, Part Three",766,"<p>While Biroc leads the Doctor to a view of the Tharil&apos;s lordly past, Romana learns more about the damaged freighter and the coldheartedness of its crew. Meanwhile Commander Rorvik, confounded by the time mirror inside the universal center gateway, ignores evidence that it&apos;s no simple mirror and decides to blast it, imperiling the lives of everyone.</p>",19,18,25,"1981-01-17",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323348/doctor-who-18x19-warriors-gate-part-three"),
(323349,"Warriors&apos; Gate, Part Four",766,"<p>After the Doctor and Romana save the Tharil race, Romana agrees to leave the Doctor to become the Tharils&apos; &quot;Queen of Time.&quot;</p>",20,18,25,"1981-01-24",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323349/doctor-who-18x20-warriors-gate-part-four"),
(323350,"The Keeper of Traken, Part One",766,"<p>Returning to N-Space, The Doctor and Adric are summoned to Traken, a planet of peace and harmony. The Keeper of Traken is nearing the end of his 1000-year-old reign and one of the Traken consuls is to become the next Keeper. The Doctor, Adric, Tremas (the Keeper Nominate) and Nyssa (his daughter) set about to stop the Melkur, a calcified figure believed to be a &quot;Source of Evil&quot; trying to destroy the Traken Union, only to later discover it is the guise of a old enemy of the Doctor - The Master - who plans to take control of The Source (the keystone of Union) so he can regenerate into a new body.</p>",21,18,25,"1981-01-31",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323350/doctor-who-18x21-the-keeper-of-traken-part-one"),
(323351,"The Keeper of Traken, Part Two",766,"<p>Tremas claims counselor privilege to protect the Doctor and Adric from execution, though it binds his fate to theirs if they&apos;re found guilty of murder. Melkur strengthens his hold over Kassia while Seron decides to have rapport with The Keeper to learn truth, and Adric finds evidence of another TARDIS in the area.</p>",22,18,25,"1981-02-07",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323351/doctor-who-18x22-the-keeper-of-traken-part-two"),
(323352,"The Keeper of Traken, Part Three",766,"<p>With Tremas falling under suspicion, due to his association with the Doctor, a new Keeper Nominate is named. Now, with everything in place, Melkur has only a short wait before his full malevolence can unfold.</p>",23,18,25,"1981-02-14",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323352/doctor-who-18x23-the-keeper-of-traken-part-three"),
(323353,"The Keeper of Traken, Part Four",766,"<p>With the merciless Melkur in control of The Source, the Doctor and his allies have only a slim chance of deposing him, which also puts the peace of the Traken Union in severe jeopardy.</p>",24,18,25,"1981-02-21",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323353/doctor-who-18x24-the-keeper-of-traken-part-four"),
(323354,"Logopolis, Part One",766,"<p>Preparing to overhaul his TARDIS, the Doctor goes to Earth to take fresh measurements of a police box. A figure in white observes, as the Master lies in wait with a puzzling predicament for his rival Time Lord.</p>",25,18,25,"1981-02-28",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323354/doctor-who-18x25-logopolis-part-one"),
(323355,"Logopolis, Part Two",766,"<p>With the threat of doom ever-present, the Doctor and Adric press on for Logopolis, where the muttered mathematical incantations of its people can completely overhaul the TARDIS. En route they discover an accidental yet demanding passenger on board while, all the while, the Master secretively journeys with them to ensnare the Doctor in a diabolical trap.</p>",26,18,25,"1981-03-07","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/350/875628.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323355/doctor-who-18x26-logopolis-part-two"),
(323356,"Logopolis, Part Three",766,"<p>With Nyssa from Traken unexpectedly rejoining the group, Adric aids the Monitor of Logopolis in trying to save the Doctor before time runs out. The Master, at liberty to prepare, is finally ready to reveal his true target, which unknowingly sets off the biggest catastrophe of all time.</p>",27,18,25,"1981-03-14","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/350/875627.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323356/doctor-who-18x27-logopolis-part-three"),
(323357,"Logopolis, Part Four",766,"<p>With the universe collapsing, the Doctor forms an uneasy alliance with the Master to save it. In case all does not go well, the Watcher takes the Doctor&apos;s companions to a safe place, but his plans for them don&apos;t stop there. The one hope for all lies back on Earth.</p>",28,18,25,"1981-03-21","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/350/875626.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323357/doctor-who-18x28-logopolis-part-four"),
(323358,"Castrovalva, Part One",766,"<p>The Doctor has regenerated but it hasn&apos;t gone well. He&apos;s mentally unraveling and needs a place to rest beyond outside influences. Unfortunately the Master has laid a trap for the TARDIS that denies the Doctor undisturbed recovery time.</p>",1,19,25,"1982-01-04","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/350/875625.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323358/doctor-who-19x01-castrovalva-part-one"),
(323359,"Castrovalva, Part Two",766,"<p>To avoid falling into Event One (the Big Bang), the Doctor must convert mass into momentum by having the TARDIS jettison a quarter of itself. Unfortunately it can not be known which rooms will be ejected.</p>",2,19,25,"1982-01-05","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/350/875624.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323359/doctor-who-19x02-castrovalva-part-two"),
(323360,"Castrovalva, Part Three",766,"<p>The city of Castrovalva and its untroubled people would seen an ideal place for the Doctor to recover, but a dire warning from Adric, held captive by The Master, makes it seen less so.</p>",3,19,25,"1982-01-11","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/350/875623.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323360/doctor-who-19x03-castrovalva-part-three"),
(323361,"Castrovalva, Part Four",766,"<p>The Doctor discovers Castrovalva is a cursive occlusion, an impossible yet manifested Escheresque environment, with all pathways, no matter which direction one goes, leading back to the same point. It is a trap laid by the Master with no apparent way out.</p>",4,19,25,"1982-01-12","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/350/875622.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323361/doctor-who-19x04-castrovalva-part-four");
REPLACE INTO episode VALUES
(323362,"Four to Doomsday, Part One",766,"<p>The arrival of the TARDIS is observed by three Urbankans via their manipticon devices. Intrigued, they begin dividing the Doctor&apos;s friends, and disguising themselves as humans.</p>",5,19,25,"1982-01-18",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323362/doctor-who-19x05-four-to-doomsday-part-one"),
(323363,"Four to Doomsday, Part Two",766,"<p>As the Doctor meets the representatives of humanity aboard the Urbankan ship, a Grecian philosopher reveals a bizarre secret about Monarch and his methods.</p>",6,19,25,"1982-01-19",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323363/doctor-who-19x06-four-to-doomsday-part-two"),
(323364,"Four to Doomsday, Part Three",766,"<p>Panicking, Tegan accidentally pilots the TARDIS into space, while Lin Fitu betrays the Doctor and Bigon to Monarch, who demands they be beheaded as punishment.</p>",7,19,25,"1982-01-25",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323364/doctor-who-19x07-four-to-doomsday-part-three"),
(323365,"Four to Doomsday, Part Four",766,"<p>The Doctor takes a dangerous spacewalk to rescue Tegan, while Nyssa and Bigon keep the Urbankans distracted and Adric decides exactly whose side he is on.</p>",8,19,25,"1982-01-26",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323365/doctor-who-19x08-four-to-doomsday-part-four"),
(323366,"Kinda, Part One",766,"<p>On Deva Loka, a sylvan paradise planet with no predators, diseases or civilized roadways, Nyssa (due to Monarch&apos;s two attempts to turn her into an android) stays in the TARDIS to fully recover from mild mental disorientation, under the Doctor&apos;s Delta Wave Augmenter while the others go exploring. The Doctor and Adric find a survey team assessing the planet for colonization, and cracking under the stress of three fellow members (half the crew) disappearing without a trace. There&apos;s also a primitive and almost entirely speechless native culture on hand who curiously have about them a few items of technically advanced skill and knowledge. Meanwhile Tegan succumbs to a dreaming tree where an evil entity awaits a catalyst for entering the real world.</p>",9,19,25,"1982-02-01",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323366/doctor-who-19x09-kinda-part-one"),
(323367,"Kinda, Part Two",766,"<p>Left in charge by Sanders, Security Man Hindle - unhinged and in complete control of the two Kinda hostages - locks up the others while he primes the dome for a 50 mile perimeter of deforestation through acid and fire, having &quot;reasoned out&quot; that the trees and plants are a threat. Adric perpetrates a ruse to help the Doctor and Todd but is caught and about to be punished when Sanders returns, a changed man. Sanders bears a gift for Hindle - a box given him by a Kinda mystic elder, which may be dangerous and which the Doctor is forced to open. Meanwhile, Tegan is shown herself in the dream world and left to determine which of her selves is real.</p>",10,19,25,"1982-02-02",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323367/doctor-who-19x10-kinda-part-two"),
(323368,"Kinda, Part Three",766,"<p>Todd and the Doctor receive a telepathic invitation to visit the Kinda&apos;s blind matriarch and her ward in a cave. Meanwhile, Hinkle is finally set to reduce the dome to its &quot;base chemical constituents&quot; but stops to relax and build a toy city. Tegan is out cold after the snake tattoo of the Mara leaves her arm to possess Aris, giving Aris voice and, through it, the ability to lead his people to their destruction.</p>",11,19,25,"1982-02-08",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323368/doctor-who-19x11-kinda-part-three"),
(323369,"Kinda, Part Four",766,"<p>With a frightening vision of what&apos;s to come from Panna (the Kinda&apos;s blind visionary), the Doctor must break Hindle&apos;s control over the Kinda hostages and stop his deforestation plan, then send the Mara back to The Dark Places of the Inside from whence it came before it can destroy the Kinda and head out to topple civilizations.</p>",12,19,25,"1982-02-09",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323369/doctor-who-19x12-kinda-part-four"),
(323370,"The Visitation, Part One",766,"<p>The TARDIS returns Tegan to Heathrow Airport: Tall trees, peaceful, clear skies, thriving vegetation and a touch of sulfur in the air. Obviously the TARDIS is a little out of date (about three hundred years or so), but upon looking around the Doctor finds there&apos;s more amiss than his navigational controls, all arising after a recent comet crash that was not on Earth&apos;s schedule.</p>",13,19,25,"1982-02-15",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323370/doctor-who-19x13-the-visitation-part-one"),
(323371,"The Visitation, Part Two",766,"<p>To rescue Tegan and Adric, captured and interrogated by the Terileptil fugitive leader, the Doctor must get past the locals under alien control and overcome Death (an android servant dressed up as The Grim Reaper).</p>",14,19,25,"1982-02-16",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323371/doctor-who-19x14-the-visitation-part-two"),
(323372,"The Visitation, Part Three",766,"<p>The Doctor makes the fugitive Terileptils a rare offer they shouldn&apos;t refuse; but, though few in numbers, they have a plan in the works for the quick and complete domination of Earth and mean to see it through.</p>",15,19,25,"1982-02-22",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323372/doctor-who-19x15-the-visitation-part-three"),
(323373,"The Visitation, Part Four",766,"<p>With Tegan and Richard under alien control, and the manor sealed against anyone leaving or entering, it&apos;s a question whether or not the Doctor can get to London before the Terileptils release their improved strain of black death upon the world.</p>",16,19,25,"1982-02-23",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/323373/doctor-who-19x16-the-visitation-part-four"),
(324236,"Black Orchid, Part One",766,"<p>A murder is committed in Cranleigh Hall .The Cranleighs ask the Doctor to play cricket and then join them for a masked ball, enabling the killer to hide in plain sight.</p>",17,19,25,"1982-03-01",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324236/doctor-who-19x17-black-orchid-part-one"),
(324237,"Black Orchid, Part Two",766,"<p>The Doctor stands accused of murder, despite Lady Cranleigh knowing he is innocent. What is the secret she is protecting that allows her to let an innocent man go to jail?</p>",18,19,25,"1982-03-02",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324237/doctor-who-19x18-black-orchid-part-two"),
(324282,"Earthshock, Part One",766,"<p>The Doctor lands the Tardis in an underground cavern on 26th century Earth. Then the Doctor, Tegan, Nyssa and Adric become embroiled in the search for a team of missing scientists being preformed by the military.</p>",19,19,25,"1982-03-08","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/105349.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324282/doctor-who-19x19-earthshock-part-one"),
(324283,"Earthshock, Part Two",766,"<p>The Doctor discovers a bomb planted by the Cybermen, disarms it and then materializes the Tardis onto a freighter orbiting the Earth where mysterious murders are also being committed.</p>",20,19,25,"1982-03-09","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/105365.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324283/doctor-who-19x20-earthshock-part-two"),
(324284,"Earthshock, Part Three",766,"<p>Captain Briggs takes the Doctor prisoner, suspecting him of being behind the murders on board. Meanwhile the Cybermen start the process of taking over the ship with the help of a traitorous crew member. The Cybermen also start reviving other Cybermen who are hidden away as cargo.</p>",21,19,25,"1982-03-15","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/105402.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324284/doctor-who-19x21-earthshock-part-three"),
(324285,"Earthshock, Part Four",766,"<p>The Cybermen have taken over the bridge of the freighter. They fit a device onto the freighters control panel that will cause the ship to explode. The ships fuel will cause a explosion so strong that it will destroy the Earth completely. The Doctor and Companions battle against the Cybermen in an attempt to foil their plan. Someone pays the ultimate price to save the Earth and crew of the freighter.</p>",22,19,25,"1982-03-16","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/105431.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324285/doctor-who-19x22-earthshock-part-four"),
(324286,"Time-Flight, Part One",766,"<p>The Doctor still dealing with Adric&apos;s death, lands the Tardis at London&apos;s Heathrow airport and soon becomes involved with a missing Concord SST.</p>",23,19,25,"1982-03-22","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/105834.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324286/doctor-who-19x23-time-flight-part-one"),
(324287,"Time-Flight, Part Two",766,"<p>The Doctor&apos;s Tardis vanishes, while tracking it down the Doctor encounters a strange being named &quot;Kalid&quot; who seems to be in control of events.</p>",24,19,25,"1982-03-23","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/105838.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324287/doctor-who-19x24-time-flight-part-two"),
(324288,"Time-Flight, Part Three",766,"<p>The Master commandeers the Doctors Tardis, leaving the Doctor behind to figure out what the alien artifact is.</p>",25,19,25,"1982-03-29","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/105843.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324288/doctor-who-19x25-time-flight-part-three"),
(324289,"Time-Flight, Part Four",766,"<p>The Doctor partially works with The Master, the crew of the Concord jury rig the plane so they can take off with the Doctor&apos;s help. The Doctor follows The Master back to Heathrow airport. The Doctor announces that the temporal limiter The Master conned him out of will need replacing and that he is going to be stuck. Tegan gets accidentally left behind at Heathrow.</p>",26,19,25,"1982-03-30","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/105844.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324289/doctor-who-19x26-time-flight-part-four"),
(324291,"Arc of Infinity, Part One",766,"<p>On Gallifrey, someone commits a treasonous act and transmits the Doctor&apos;s bio-extract from The Matrix to a unknown being. Meanwhile on Earth, two students spend the night in a underground crypt in Amsterdam and are attacked by a alien creature.</p>",1,20,25,"1983-01-04","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/105863.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324291/doctor-who-20x01-arc-of-infinity-part-one"),
(324292,"Arc of Infinity, Part Two",766,"<p>With a anti-matter being trying to enter the universe through the Doctor, the Gallifreyan high council see&apos;s only one clear course of action. They decided to put the Doctor to death in order to prevent the occurrence.</p>",2,20,25,"1983-01-05","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/105869.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324292/doctor-who-20x02-arc-of-infinity-part-two"),
(324293,"Arc of Infinity, Part Three",766,"<p>The Council follows through with their death order and Omega holds the Doctor in Limbo. Commander Maxil discover&apos;s that Nyssa was right and the Doctors Bio-Extract had been transmitted from The Matrix.Tegan finds her cousin who is under alien control.</p>",3,20,25,"1983-01-11","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/105871.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324293/doctor-who-20x03-arc-of-infinity-part-three"),
(324294,"Arc of Infinity, Part Four",766,"<p>The Doctor having returned to Earth, finds Omega&apos;s Tardis and is not able to prevent Omega&apos;s transfer upon arrival. Omega being of anti-matter and unstable is on the verge of destroying the planet in his attempt to regain a body.</p>",4,20,25,"1983-01-12","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/105888.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324294/doctor-who-20x04-arc-of-infinity-part-four"),
(324295,"Snakedance, Part One",766,"<p>The Tardis lands on the home world of the Sumaran civilization. The Doctor did not set the co-ordinates for the landing and discovers that Tegan did. He starts questioning if the Mara is still active inside of her from their previous adventure on the Kinda world.</p>",5,20,25,"1983-01-18","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/105901.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324295/doctor-who-20x05-snakedance-part-one"),
(324296,"Snakedance, Part Two",766,"<p>The Doctor finds out about the legend of the Mara&apos;s return. Tegan goes into the cave and see&apos;s a Mara skull in one of the mirrors. Tegan summons Lon to her.</p>",6,20,25,"1983-01-19","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/105909.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324296/doctor-who-20x06-snakedance-part-two"),
(324297,"Snakedance, Part Three",766,"<p>Possessed Tegan and Lon try to find the location of the Great Crystal. The Doctor finds himself in prison with only Nyssa to get him out while Chela tells the Doctor about Dojjen and gives him Dojjen&apos;s journal.</p>",7,20,25,"1983-01-25","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/105914.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324297/doctor-who-20x07-snakedance-part-three"),
(324298,"Snakedance, Part Four",766,"<p>The Mara&apos;s plan is close to fruition, the Doctor comes to prevent the Mara from finalizing the plan with the knowledge that Dojjen imparted to him.</p>",8,20,25,"1983-01-26","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/105918.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324298/doctor-who-20x08-snakedance-part-four"),
(324299,"Mawdryn Undead, Part One",766,"<p>The Black Guardian strikes a deal with a school student named Turlough to kill the Doctor. He promises him that he will take him back to his home planet if he does the job. Meanwhile The Doctor&apos;s Tardis is trapped by a hidden device near Turlough&apos;s school.</p>",9,20,25,"1983-02-01","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/106747.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324299/doctor-who-20x09-mawdryn-undead-part-one"),
(324300,"Mawdryn Undead, Part Two",766,"<p>The Doctor is stranded on Earth in 1983 while Tegan and Nyssa are looking for him in 1977. Tegan and Nyssa encounter a injured man they believe to be the doctor. Both the Doctor And Tegan and Nyssa encounter Brigadier Lethbridge Stewart who seems to have no memory of The Doctor.</p>",10,20,25,"1983-02-02","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/106748.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324300/doctor-who-20x10-mawdryn-undead-part-two"),
(324301,"Mawdryn Undead, Part Three",766,"<p>The Doctor travels to the orbiting spaceship with the Brigadier. Soon to discover a piece of Timelord technology on board the ship. Tegan and Turlough travel to the ship with their version of the Brigadier.</p>",11,20,25,"1983-02-08","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/106750.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324301/doctor-who-20x11-mawdryn-undead-part-three"),
(324302,"Mawdryn Undead, Part Four",766,"<p>The Doctor is on the ship and his future looks bleak as he is about to loose all his Timelord abilities to the Mawdryn. Both the Brigadiers come in to the Mawdryns room with the Timelord artifact right as the transfer is starting.</p>",12,20,25,"1983-02-09","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/106751.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324302/doctor-who-20x12-mawdryn-undead-part-four"),
(324303,"Terminus, Part One",766,"<p>Turlough sabotages the Tardis under the Black Guardian&apos;s direction and the Tardis materializes in the nearest ship. Nyssa is trapped in her room and has to escape into the spaceship the Tardis&apos;s emergency circuits have landed it on.</p>",13,20,25,"1983-02-15","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/106758.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324303/doctor-who-20x13-terminus-part-one"),
(324304,"Terminus, Part Two",766,"<p>The two people the Doctor meets who have broken into the ship realize that they are on Terminus, where people who have the Lazar disease are sent to die. The Doctor finds it strange that the ship is at the exact center of the universe.</p>",14,20,25,"1983-02-16","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/106760.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324304/doctor-who-20x14-terminus-part-two"),
(324305,"Terminus, Part Three",766,"<p>The guards think the Doctor and those with him are investigators since they are not Lazars and are armed. Nyssa is taken off to be treated for the disease by the Garm.</p>",15,20,25,"1983-02-22","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/106761.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324305/doctor-who-20x15-terminus-part-three"),
(324306,"Terminus, Part Four",766,"<p>The Doctor discovers that the pilot had dumped the ships fuel billions of years ago and that the ship is going into another automatic fuel dump sequence because of the damaged engine. He determines that if the fuel gets dumped into space again, it will cause the destruction of the universe. Nyssa makes a decision that affects everyone.</p>",16,20,25,"1983-02-23","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/106759.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324306/doctor-who-20x16-terminus-part-four"),
(324307,"Enlightenment, Part One",766,"<p>The Doctor receives a warning from the White Guardian and is given co-ordinates to materialize the Tardis at. He lands the Tardis on a ship Captained by one of the Eternals. A Clairvoyant race that never dies and plays games involving mortals to relieve their boredom.</p>",17,20,25,"1983-03-01","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/106775.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324307/doctor-who-20x17-enlightenment-part-one"),
(324308,"Enlightenment, Part Two",766,"<p>Captain Striker reveals to the Doctor that they are Eternal&apos;s and that they use ephemeral beings. The Black Guardian gets harsher with Turlough. The Captain takes the Tardis away from the Doctor.</p>",18,20,25,"1983-03-02","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/106779.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324308/doctor-who-20x18-enlightenment-part-two"),
(324309,"Enlightenment, Part Three",766,"<p>Captain Wrack rescues Turlough and see&apos;s his coming aboard as a opportunity to invite all the other Captains over and use their visit to her advantage.</p>",19,20,25,"1983-03-08","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/106871.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324309/doctor-who-20x19-enlightenment-part-three"),
(324310,"Enlightenment, Part Four",766,"<p>Captain Wrack sets Tegan up to destroy Striker and his ship without her knowing it. Tegan convinces Captain Wrack to send the Doctor back to Striker&apos;s ship where the Doctor works to foil her plot and defeat the Black Guardian.</p>",20,20,25,"1983-03-09","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/42/106880.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324310/doctor-who-20x20-enlightenment-part-four"),
(324311,"The King&apos;s Demons, Part One",766,"<p>The Doctor lands the Tardis in 1215 England at the Castle of Ranulf Fitzwilliam in the middle of a jousting tournament and the Doctor is immediately hailed as a demon by the king. The Doctor finds this very suspicious. SPOILER ALERT: If you are watching this episode for the first time, wait until it is over to view the main cast as that will give some of the plot away.</p>",21,20,25,"1983-03-15","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/44/111805.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324311/doctor-who-20x21-the-kings-demons-part-one"),
(324312,"The King&apos;s Demons, Part Two",766,"<p>The Doctor having discovered that The Master is behind the false King, works to stop the Master from preventing the Magna Carta to be signed.</p>",22,20,25,"1983-03-16","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/44/111808.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324312/doctor-who-20x22-the-kings-demons-part-two"),
(324314,"Warriors of the Deep, Part One",766,"<p>The Doctor materializes the TARDIS inside a underwater military base in 2084 during wartime. The base is about to be attacked on two fronts, secret agents within and a unknown enemy outside of the base.</p>",1,21,25,"1984-01-05","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/46/115872.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324314/doctor-who-21x01-warriors-of-the-deep-part-one"),
(324315,"Warriors of the Deep, Part Two",766,"<p>Just as the doctor is starting to gain a tentative trust from the humans of the underwater military base, an unknown cruiser appears and the Doctor seems to recognize it and warns the humans not to fire upon it.</p>",2,21,25,"1984-01-06","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/46/115894.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324315/doctor-who-21x02-warriors-of-the-deep-part-two"),
(324316,"Warriors of the Deep, Part Three",766,"<p>While the Silurians and Sea Devils attack the bases air locks, the saboteurs take advantage of the distraction to go ahead with their own plans.</p><p></p>",3,21,25,"1984-01-12","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/46/115895.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324316/doctor-who-21x03-warriors-of-the-deep-part-three"),
(324317,"Warriors of the Deep, Part Four",766,"<p>The Doctor is presented with a moral dilemma when Icthar reveals his plans to get rid of the human race so the Silurians can take back what was once theirs.</p>",4,21,25,"1984-01-13","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/46/115897.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324317/doctor-who-21x04-warriors-of-the-deep-part-four"),
(324330,"The Awakening, Part One",766,"<p>The TARDIS arrives in Little Hodcombe, Tegan wants to visit her Grandfather while they are there. Also, a war re-enactment is going on that starts to get more and more out of hand and realistic for unknown reasons.</p>",5,21,25,"1984-01-19","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/46/116969.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324330/doctor-who-21x05-the-awakening-part-one"),
(324331,"The Awakening, Part Two",766,"<p>The Malus is forcing the towns people to preform the re-enactment for real as it needs the psychic forces created by the suffering of war to feed off of and recharge it&apos;s energies. It is up to the Doctor to prevent the Malus plans from reaching fruition.</p>",6,21,25,"1984-01-20","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/46/116970.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324331/doctor-who-21x06-the-awakening-part-two"),
(324332,"Frontios, Part One",766,"<p>In the far distant future, the few remaining survivors of the human race struggle to survive on the planet Frontios. The Doctor states that the Laws of time do not allow him to have contact because the survivors must go their own way without outside intervention at this key point in time.A meteor storm hits the planet and starts to drag the TARDIS down with it, the Doctor is unable to stop the TARDIS from making a emergency landing.</p>",7,21,25,"1984-01-26","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/46/116990.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324332/doctor-who-21x07-frontios-part-one"),
(324333,"Frontios, Part Two",766,"<p>The Doctor works to help the injured colonist, Tegan discovers a file in a closed drawer called &quot;Deaths Unaccountable&quot;. Meanwhile, Plantagenate works to convict the Doctor of being the source of the attacks on Frontios.</p>",8,21,25,"1984-01-27","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/46/117105.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324333/doctor-who-21x08-frontios-part-two"),
(324334,"Frontios, Part Three",766,"<p>Turlough starts to regain ancestral memories of the Tractators, the Doctor having discovered the Tractators works to discover what their plan is.</p>",9,21,25,"1984-02-02","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/46/117120.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324334/doctor-who-21x09-frontios-part-three"),
(324335,"Frontios, Part Four",766,"<p>The Doctor tries to deal with the Tractator&apos;s cunning plan, despite Turlough&apos;s best intervention. They discover the splintered TARDIS in the tunnels beneath the planet&apos;s surface, but how will they put it together again?</p>",10,21,25,"1984-02-03","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/46/117148.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324335/doctor-who-21x10-frontios-part-four"),
(324337,"Resurrection of the Daleks, Part One",766,"<p>The Doctor starts having problems navigating the TARDIS through the space-time vortex and ends up on Earth in the future where strange events are going on with imitation police officers and soldiers from the future.</p>",11,21,50,"1984-02-08","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/47/118612.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324337/doctor-who-21x11-resurrection-of-the-daleks-part-one"),
(324339,"Resurrection of the Daleks, Part Two",766,"<p>The Daleks capture the Doctor and plan to duplicate him and his companions as part of their plan to attack the high Council of Gallifrey. Davros starts converting Daleks and their helpers over to his control.</p>",12,21,50,"1984-02-15","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/47/118687.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324339/doctor-who-21x12-resurrection-of-the-daleks-part-two"),
(324342,"Planet of Fire, Part One",766,"<p>The Tardis receives a distress signal and at the same time Kamelion seems to be having problems while linked into the Tardis. Following the distress signal the Doctor arrives on Lanzarote and Turlough rescues Peri. Turlough seems to know where the distress signal is coming from.</p>",13,21,25,"1984-02-23","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/52/130500.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324342/doctor-who-21x13-planet-of-fire-part-one"),
(324343,"Planet of Fire, Part Two",766,"<p>The Master strengthens his control over Kamelion in order to be able to complete his goals and tries to get Peri under his control.</p>",14,21,25,"1984-02-24","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/52/130505.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324343/doctor-who-21x14-planet-of-fire-part-two"),
(324344,"Planet of Fire, Part Three",766,"<p>Turlough is taken to his fathers ship, the Doctor and The Master battle for control of Kamelion so The Master can go through with his plan.</p>",15,21,25,"1984-03-01","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/52/130509.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324344/doctor-who-21x15-planet-of-fire-part-three"),
(324345,"Planet of Fire, Part Four",766,"<p>In order to complete his plan to bring himself back to full size after his accident with his tissue compression eliminator, The Master tries to destroy the Doctor. Turlough makes a decision and tells the Doctor why he was exiled to Earth.</p>",16,21,25,"1984-03-02","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/52/130516.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324345/doctor-who-21x16-planet-of-fire-part-four"),
(324346,"The Caves of Androzani, Part One",766,"<p>The Doctor lands on one of the twin planets of Androzani where he along with Peri are mistaken for gun runners and sentenced to death.</p>",17,21,25,"1984-03-08","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/52/130531.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324346/doctor-who-21x17-the-caves-of-androzani-part-one"),
(324347,"The Caves of Androzani, Part Two",766,"<p>Sharez Jek and his androids save the Doctor and Peri from execution when he rescues them. Then he takes a shine to Peri and wants her with him forever. Later the Doctor and Peri find out they are dying from Spectrox Toxemia, having been poisoned when they handled the Spectrox nest upon first entering the cave system.</p>",18,21,25,"1984-03-09","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/57/143718.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324347/doctor-who-21x18-the-caves-of-androzani-part-two"),
(324348,"The Caves of Androzani, Part Three",766,"<p>The Doctor escapes the Mag,a creature and is taken prisoner by the gun runners; The real Salateen takes Peri back to General Challek and is then kidnapped again by Sharaz Jek.</p>",19,21,25,"1984-03-15","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/57/143807.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324348/doctor-who-21x19-the-caves-of-androzani-part-three"),
(324349,"The Caves of Androzani, Part Four",766,"<p>Chellak and his men attack Jek&apos;s base. The Dr. crash-lands the ship, and must escape from his captors to find the antidote to the Spectrox poisoning and save Peri. He does so, but at a staggering cost.</p>",20,21,25,"1984-03-16","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/57/143887.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324349/doctor-who-21x20-the-caves-of-androzani-part-four"),
(324350,"The Twin Dilemma, Part One",766,"<p>The twin human children Romulus and Remus are kidnapped by the mysterious professor Edgeworth. The Children appear to be genius&apos;s. Meanwhile the Doctor seems to be having stability problems with his new regeneration and is acting erratically.</p>",21,21,25,"1984-03-22","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/64/161816.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324350/doctor-who-21x21-the-twin-dilemma-part-one"),
(324351,"The Twin Dilemma, Part Two",766,"<p>The Doctor and Perry arrive at the facility on Titan 3 where Romulus and Remus are being held. The Doctor is taken prisoner by one of the Professors guards. When the Doctor is brought to the professor he recognizes him as Azmael the Master of Jaconda.</p>",22,21,25,"1984-03-23","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/118/295902.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324351/doctor-who-21x22-the-twin-dilemma-part-two"),
(324353,"The Twin Dilemma, Part Three",766,"<p>The Doctor, Peri and Hugo Lang arrive on Jaconda only to discover the massive devastation that the planet has suffered. Azmael is told about the destruction of the Titan 3 outpost.</p>",23,21,25,"1984-03-29","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/118/295903.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324353/doctor-who-21x23-the-twin-dilemma-part-three"),
(324354,"The Twin Dilemma, Part Four",766,"<p>The Doctor attempts to halt Mestor&apos;s true plan for the planet of Jaconda, Azmael has a decision to make for his world.</p>",24,21,25,"1984-03-30","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/118/295916.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324354/doctor-who-21x24-the-twin-dilemma-part-four"),
(324356,"Attack of the Cybermen, Part One",766,"<p>The Doctor and Peri investigate strange signals, in the process, The Tardis lands at the spot where it all began. I.M. Formemans junk yard on Totters Lane. The Doctor is followed by some odd policemen. After landing, he works on the TARDIS&apos;s Chameleon circuit and the TARDIS starts to change shape but seems to have a bit of trouble blending in after such a long time of not working.</p>",1,22,45,"1985-01-05","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/118/295919.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324356/doctor-who-22x01-attack-of-the-cybermen-part-one"),
(324358,"Attack of the Cybermen, Part Two",766,"<p>The Doctor discovers that the Cybermen are involved with the strange distress signal. Peri and the Doctor discover who Lytton is working for and do their best to keep the Cybermen from gaining time travel.</p>",2,22,45,"1985-01-12","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/118/295933.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324358/doctor-who-22x02-attack-of-the-cybermen-part-two"),
(324360,"Vengeance on Varos, Part One",766,"<p>After having power supply problems with the TARDIS, the Doctor and Peri land on the planet Varos where their leaders are punished by the citizens on National television when they are displeased with the leaders actions. The Doctor quickly becomes a fugitive.</p>",3,22,45,"1985-01-19","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/118/296118.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324360/doctor-who-22x03-vengeance-on-varos-part-one"),
(324361,"Vengeance on Varos, Part Two",766,null,4,22,45,"1985-01-26","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/118/296123.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324361/doctor-who-22x04-vengeance-on-varos-part-two"),
(324363,"The Mark of the Rani, Part One",766,null,5,22,45,"1985-02-02","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/116/291193.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324363/doctor-who-22x05-the-mark-of-the-rani-part-one"),
(324364,"The Mark of the Rani, Part Two",766,null,6,22,45,"1985-02-09","https://static.tvmaze.com/uploads/images/medium_landscape/116/291197.jpg","https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324364/doctor-who-22x06-the-mark-of-the-rani-part-two"),
(324365,"The Two Doctors, Part One",766,null,7,22,45,"1985-02-16",null,"https://www.tvmaze.com/episodes/324365/doctor-who-22x07-the-two-doctors-part-one"),
